org.stekikun.dolmen.syntax

Interface Regular.Folder<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - the resulting type of applying this folder
    Enclosing class:
    Regular

    public static interface Regular.Folder<V>
    An instance of Regular.Folder is a set of methods to apply to the various cases of a regular expression, depending on its form, as part of a (possibly) recursive traversal of the regular expression structure. It is the natural catamorphism of the tree-like structure of regular expressions, and a generalization of the traditional Java visitor.
